  <para>
    <command>Elkcepsed</command> is the opposite of <link
    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.PixelSelection.Despeckle"><command>Despeckle</command></link>.
    Instead of filling holes in the selection by selecting more
    pixels, it deselects small islands and peninsulas of of selected
    pixels.  Compare to <link
    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.PixelSelection.Despeckle"><command>Despeckle</command></link>,
    which fills in small holes in the selection.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>microstructure</varname> parameter specifies the &micro;
    where the selection resides.
  </para>
  <para>
    The algorithm works by recursively deselecting all selecting
    pixels with fewer than <varname>neighbors</varname> selected
    neighbors.  Values greater than 4 are prohibited because they will
    always deselect the entire &micro;.  For examples, see <xref
      linkend="Figure-elkcepsed"/>.
  </para>
